notes: very young specimen and difficult to identify. The gills do not meet beneath the abdomen and the sclerotised anal ridge is marginal, excluding it from the albertae-group. Possibly E. margarita (this is the type locality of that species), but the dorsal flanges on the femora are rounded rather than sharply pointed.
